","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that getting this signal doesn’t itself guarantee that the value of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"explicitNotify","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then any call to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_set_property()"},{"type":"text","text":" results"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"type":"text","text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If they did pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"explicitNotify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then this signal is emitted only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when they explicitly call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify()"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and common practice is to do that only when the value has actually changed."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This signal is typically used to obtain change notification for a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single property, by specifying the property name as a detail in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_connect()"},{"text":" call, like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["g_signal_connect (text_view->buffer, \"notify::paste-target-list\",","                  G_CALLBACK (gtk_text_view_target_list_notify),","                  text_view